messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] Worm snakes
messages.messageBody:
<<They are tiny little snakes that are easily mistaken for earth worms.
They
are pinkish-lavender colored. In the Spring, they invade our house
coming
in through the master bath somewhere. Danny (3) goes on snake
expeditions
daily, flipping over all the bath mats.

I really kind of like them, but most people around here don't.

Julie>>

I was told that these are rare, I've only seen one when we lived in San
Diego and it was injured. I guess they aren't as rare as this person
stated.

Kris

messages.messageBody:
They are tiny little snakes that are easily mistaken for earth worms. They
are pinkish-lavender colored. In the Spring, they invade our house coming
in through the master bath somewhere. Danny (3) goes on snake expeditions
daily, flipping over all the bath mats.

I really kind of like them, but most people around here don't.

Julie
